WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.560 --> 00:00:05.750
In A Song of Ice and Fire and Game of Thrones,
the Stark family've ruled the north for thousands

00:00:05.750 --> 00:00:10.940
of years – as Kings of Winter , then as
Wardens of the North after Aegon came.

00:00:10.940 --> 00:00:14.510
Things change in the first book and season
of Thrones, when the Lord of Winterfell Ned

00:00:14.510 --> 00:00:17.860
Stark is imprisoned and executed by King Joffrey.

00:00:17.860 --> 00:00:22.380
Ned’s son Robb marches south with an army,
and the north secedes from the Seven Kingdoms,

00:00:22.380 --> 00:00:27.390
declaring Robb King in the North and the riverlands
– the first Stark King in three hundred

00:00:27.390 --> 00:00:28.390
years.

00:00:28.390 --> 00:00:30.039
But this doesn't last long.

00:00:30.039 --> 00:00:34.850
Winterfell is captured by Theon Greyjoy , then
burned by Ramsay Snow , and the Stark kids

00:00:34.850 --> 00:00:35.850
scatter.

00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:39.980
Robb's campaign falters, and he's killed at
the Red Wedding by the Boltons and the Freys

00:00:39.980 --> 00:00:45.210
– Roose Bolton is made Warden of the North
. So for the first time in thousands of years,

00:00:45.210 --> 00:00:48.190
the north is no longer ruled by a Stark.

00:00:48.190 --> 00:00:50.030
Is this the end for the Kings of Winter?

00:00:50.030 --> 00:00:53.390
Or does the north remember?

00:00:53.390 --> 00:00:57.480
In Season 6 of the Game of Thrones show, the
Starks make a quick comeback.

00:00:57.480 --> 00:01:01.500
Jon and Sansa take Winterfell from the Boltons,
Jon is named King, and the north is again

00:01:01.500 --> 00:01:03.480
ruled by a Stark – or a Snow.

00:01:03.480 --> 00:01:08.469
Or a Targaryen – or a Sand, depending on
who’s keeping score – but the point is,

00:01:08.469 --> 00:01:10.810
in the books, none of this has happened.

00:01:10.810 --> 00:01:15.990
By Dance’s end, Jon’s still dead, Sansa's
still in the Vale, Arya’s still in Braavos,

00:01:15.990 --> 00:01:20.929
Bran’s still a tree, Rickon’s apparently
on the island of Skagos, and Stannis Baratheon

00:01:20.929 --> 00:01:26.049
is still alive, with his army, marching against
the Boltons in Winterfell.

00:01:26.049 --> 00:01:30.069
While Stannis has some of the north on his
side, most houses officially support the Boltons

00:01:30.069 --> 00:01:34.439
and their allies the Freys . But unlike the
straightforward story of the show, the books

00:01:34.439 --> 00:01:40.000
lay out a massively complex political situation
in the north, with dozens of important players,

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:45.549
each with their own motivations, ambitions,
loyalties, secrets, loves and hates and hopes.

00:01:45.549 --> 00:01:49.819
Fans have written hundreds of thousands of
words of analysis and theories and predictions

00:01:49.819 --> 00:01:54.630
on this, many claiming that that most of the
northern houses are secretly plotting to usurp

00:01:54.630 --> 00:02:00.259
the Boltons and restore a Stark to Winterfell
– this idea’s called the Grand Northern

00:02:00.259 --> 00:02:02.329
Conspiracy.

00:02:02.329 --> 00:02:07.119
The lords of the north have a lot of good
reasons to support the Starks over the Boltons.

00:02:07.119 --> 00:02:10.979
The Starks have ruled the north for thousands
of years, and people seem to think that they’ve

00:02:10.979 --> 00:02:15.960
done a good job . Historically they’ve defended
the north from raiders, slavers, Andals, wargs

00:02:15.960 --> 00:02:20.239
and wildlings, and it supposedly was a Stark
who built the Wall to protect the north from

00:02:20.239 --> 00:02:21.680
white walkers.

00:02:21.680 --> 00:02:26.299
More recently, Ned Stark in particular was
renowned for his sense of honour and justice,

00:02:26.299 --> 00:02:30.840
winning great respect and loyalty from many
people in the north . Barbrey Dustin says

00:02:30.840 --> 00:02:32.420
“the northmen … love the Starks”.

00:02:32.420 --> 00:02:37.560
But the Boltons – not so much . The Boltons
are infamous for flaying their enemies and

00:02:37.560 --> 00:02:42.769
wearing their skins as cloaks . Their Lord
Roose is cruel, cold and creepy, known for

00:02:42.769 --> 00:02:48.310
his habit of leeching , and his son Ramsay
is a straight-up psycho, a murderous “beast

00:02:48.310 --> 00:02:53.220
in human skin” who hunts and rapes women
for sport . The Boltons commit terrible crimes

00:02:53.220 --> 00:02:57.839
against the north in order to take control
– Ramsay betrays and kills northmen at Winterfell

00:02:57.839 --> 00:03:00.120
, and kills the Lady of Hornwood.

00:03:00.120 --> 00:03:03.670
Roose sends northern armies to a suicide mission
at Duskendale.

00:03:03.670 --> 00:03:07.689
And at the Red Wedding, the Boltons betray
King Robb, participating in the breaking of

00:03:07.689 --> 00:03:10.569
guest right, and the slaughter of hundreds
of northmen.

00:03:10.569 --> 00:03:16.140
“Every lord at Winterfell lost” family
at the Red Wedding – and “the north remembers”.

00:03:16.140 --> 00:03:20.840
So the northern lords have plenty of motivation
to oppose the Boltons and restore the Starks

00:03:20.840 --> 00:03:22.040
to power.

00:03:22.040 --> 00:03:25.299
What evidence is there of a conspiracy?

00:03:25.299 --> 00:03:30.299
We know for a fact that Lord Wyman of House
Manderly is plotting against the Boltons and

00:03:30.299 --> 00:03:31.299
Freys.

00:03:31.299 --> 00:03:35.400
He pretends to be on their side, but in Dance,
he secretly meets with Davos Seaworth and

00:03:35.400 --> 00:03:39.650
gives an awesome speech about “the debt”
the Manderlys owe to the Starks , and about

00:03:39.650 --> 00:03:44.359
the “murder” of Wyman’s son Wendel at
the Red Wedding . He says “The north remembers,

00:03:44.359 --> 00:03:47.840
and the mummer’s farce is almost done”.

00:03:47.840 --> 00:03:51.909
Wyman reveals that with the help of an ironborn
boy called Wex, Wyman’s learned the truth

00:03:51.909 --> 00:03:56.680
of the sack of Winterfell – that it wasn’t
Theon Greyjoy, but Ramsay Bolton who burned

00:03:56.680 --> 00:04:00.599
the castle and killed its people, and that
Bran and Rickon Stark weren’t killed by

00:04:00.599 --> 00:04:03.519
Theon, but are still alive.

00:04:03.519 --> 00:04:07.060
Apparently Rickon is on Skagos, an island
up near the Wall.

00:04:07.060 --> 00:04:11.019
Wyman tells Davos to go there and fetch Rickon,
so that the north can rally around the young

00:04:11.019 --> 00:04:13.129
Stark and oppose the Boltons.

00:04:13.129 --> 00:04:18.269
If Davos does this, Wyman says, he’ll accept
Stannis as his King – with Rickon Stark

00:04:18.269 --> 00:04:21.989
as Lord of Winterfell – that seems to be
the plan.

00:04:21.989 --> 00:04:26.590
So Manderly is plotting against the Boltons,
and other houses are in on it too.

00:04:26.590 --> 00:04:30.520
Robett Glover is at the meeting with Davos,
and he may be in touch with his brother Lord

00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:35.729
Galbart – there are even hints Robett may
raise an army . Wyman says Houses Locke and

00:04:35.729 --> 00:04:39.660
Flint of Widow’s Watch follow his lead , and
we do see someone from House Locke speak up

00:04:39.660 --> 00:04:44.432
against Ramsay . So it seems Houses Locke,
Flint and Glover are – at least to some

00:04:44.432 --> 00:04:47.100
extent – a part of Manderly’s conspiracy.

00:04:47.100 --> 00:04:50.500
It’s also possible that House Umber is involved.

00:04:50.500 --> 00:04:54.630
The Umbers appear to be split down the middle
– half of them, under “Crowfood” Umber,

00:04:54.630 --> 00:04:58.669
side with Stannis, while the other half, under
“Whoresbane” Umber, side with the Boltons

00:04:58.669 --> 00:05:03.880
. But it’s made clear that Whoresbane isn’t
really loyal to Roose – he only joins the

00:05:03.880 --> 00:05:08.490
Boltons cause the Freys hold his nephew the
Greatjon captive . Roose says the Umbers are

00:05:08.490 --> 00:05:12.930
“cunning” and that he fears them and he
probably should – cause back in Clash, the

00:05:12.930 --> 00:05:17.890
Umbers are ordered to work with the Manderlys
to build a fleet of warships and in Dance,

00:05:17.890 --> 00:05:21.480
we see the fleet complete – “hidden”
up the White Knife river.

00:05:21.480 --> 00:05:26.190
So given that we know the Umbers have been
working on a secret fleet with the Manderlys,

00:05:26.190 --> 00:05:30.330
and that they’re not really loyal to the
Boltons, it seems very plausible that the

00:05:30.330 --> 00:05:32.660
Umbers are in on Wyman’s conspiracy.

00:05:32.660 --> 00:05:37.490
There’s further evidence for this in the
Dance chapters in Winterfell, where all the

00:05:37.490 --> 00:05:42.230
Boltons and Freys and their supposed northern
allies are cooped up together in the castle,

00:05:42.230 --> 00:05:47.280
with snowstorms and Stannis coming outside,
while tensions slowly rise.

00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:50.789
There’s this one bit where it’s mentioned
that someone makes snowmen shaped like four

00:05:50.789 --> 00:05:56.370
particular northern lords – Wyman Manderly,
Whoresbane Umber, Harwood Stout, and Barbrey

00:05:56.370 --> 00:06:02.280
Dustin . There’s pretty strong evidence
that these four snowmen represent a conspiracy

00:06:02.280 --> 00:06:03.539
in Winterfell.

00:06:03.539 --> 00:06:08.600
At one point we see Harwood Stout, who’s
the sworn man of Barbrey Dustin, talking quietly

00:06:08.600 --> 00:06:12.389
with Whoresbane Umber, who we know has been
working with Wyman.

00:06:12.389 --> 00:06:17.090
After this conversation, Barbrey becomes strangely
interested in the Winterfell crypts, and gets

00:06:17.090 --> 00:06:22.190
Theon to take her down there . The crypts
are the ancient resting place of dead Starks,

00:06:22.190 --> 00:06:25.320
each represented by a statue holding a sword.

00:06:25.320 --> 00:06:29.470
Barbrey notices that three of these swords
are missing . The significance of this is

00:06:29.470 --> 00:06:34.550
that these three missing swords are the swords
taken by Osha, Meera and Bran when they escape

00:06:34.550 --> 00:06:40.020
Winterfell . These three missing swords prove
Wex’s story that Bran and Rickon are alive,

00:06:40.020 --> 00:06:43.420
and that the Boltons lie about the sack of
Winterfell.

00:06:43.420 --> 00:06:47.130
The fact that Barbrey searches the crypts
in the first place suggests that she heard

00:06:47.130 --> 00:06:52.060
Wex’s story from Wyman – possibly through
the conversation that Harwood has with Whoresbane.

00:06:52.060 --> 00:06:57.060
Further, we know from White Harbor that Wyman
uses long visits to the privy to disguise

00:06:57.060 --> 00:07:01.790
secret meetings, and it’s hinted he continues
to do this at Winterfell.

00:07:01.790 --> 00:07:07.349
So the evidence is strong that Wyman, Harwood,
Barbrey and Whoresbane are conspiring in Winterfell

00:07:07.349 --> 00:07:11.910
– discussing Wex’s story about Bran and
Rickon, and Manderly’s plans to restore

00:07:11.910 --> 00:07:13.560
House Stark.

00:07:13.560 --> 00:07:17.960
After Barbrey visits the crypts, she speaks
out boldly to the Freys about the people killed

00:07:17.960 --> 00:07:19.169
at the Red Wedding.

00:07:19.169 --> 00:07:25.789
She parts her lips “in a thin, feral smile”
and says “The north remembers”.

00:07:25.789 --> 00:07:29.850
So that’s one part of the Grand Northern
Conspiracy – Wyman Manderly, Robett Glover,

00:07:29.850 --> 00:07:34.360
Whoresbane Umber, and Barbrey Dustin, along
with the Lockes and Flints, appear to be plotting

00:07:34.360 --> 00:07:37.870
to betray the Boltons and make Rickon Stark
Lord of Winterfell.

00:07:37.870 --> 00:07:42.790
But there’s whole other part to the conspiracy,
which takes place to the south, with its roots

00:07:42.790 --> 00:07:44.770
in events of the past.

00:07:44.770 --> 00:07:49.930
In the second book, Robb Stark says that if
he dies, he wants Jon Snow to follow him as

00:07:49.930 --> 00:07:54.650
King in the North . At this point, Sansa is
married to Tyrion Lannister, and Robb believes

00:07:54.650 --> 00:07:59.100
Arya, Bran and Rickon to be dead . So he decides
that the best course of action is to legitimise

00:07:59.100 --> 00:08:03.610
Jon as a Stark , and have him follow Robb
as King if he dies.

00:08:03.610 --> 00:08:07.199
Later that chapter, Robb meets with some of
his lords and gets them to sign a document

00:08:07.199 --> 00:08:12.430
to declare Jon his heir . Now that Robb is
dead, the question is – who knows about

00:08:12.430 --> 00:08:18.300
this will, and what plans might be underway
to carry it out and make Jon King?

00:08:18.300 --> 00:08:22.419
The people who were present at the signing
of the will include Catelyn Stark, Edmure

00:08:22.419 --> 00:08:27.020
Tully, Greatjon Umber, Jason Mallister, Maege
Mormont, and Galbart Glover.

00:08:27.020 --> 00:08:31.400
The Greatjon and Jason are both prisoners
, so they probably can’t do much, but Maege

00:08:31.400 --> 00:08:36.169
and Galbart are sent on a mission to Howland
Reed in the Neck – and it seems as though

00:08:36.169 --> 00:08:40.639
they do arrive, cause the crannogmen follow
up on some orders Robb gives about Moat Cailin

00:08:40.639 --> 00:08:46.329
. So Maege and Galbart seem to be with Howland
in the Neck, and this offers a lot of opportunities

00:08:46.329 --> 00:08:50.660
for scheming, cause not only are Maege and
Galbart some of the only people in Westeros

00:08:50.660 --> 00:08:55.080
who know that Jon Snow is the rightful King
in the North, but Howland Reed is the only

00:08:55.080 --> 00:08:59.170
living survivor of the fight at the Tower
of Joy years ago, where it was discovered

00:08:59.170 --> 00:09:04.790
that Jon is the son of Lyanna Stark and Rhaegar
Targaryen – potentially giving Jon a claim

00:09:04.790 --> 00:09:07.410
on the Iron Throne of all Westeros.

00:09:07.410 --> 00:09:12.079
That is a lot of super-important information
in one place, and there’re some hints that

00:09:12.079 --> 00:09:15.240
this information is being put into action.

00:09:15.240 --> 00:09:20.360
This involves another witness to Robb’s
will – Catelyn Stark.

00:09:20.360 --> 00:09:24.880
Catelyn dies at the Red Wedding, but in the
books, she’s resurrected by Beric Dondarrion

00:09:24.880 --> 00:09:30.870
and becomes Lady Stoneheart , a terrible vengeful
spirit who leads the brotherhood without banners

00:09:30.870 --> 00:09:36.600
down a dark and murderous path , killing everyone
even remotely connected to the Red Wedding.

00:09:36.600 --> 00:09:41.560
But Stoneheart’s not just a brutal killer,
there’s definite method to her murder.

00:09:41.560 --> 00:09:46.140
During the siege of Riverrun, a singer called
Tom of Sevenstreams spies for the brotherhood

00:09:46.140 --> 00:09:50.560
in the Lannister-Frey camp – he lets the
brotherhood know when certain Freys are travelling

00:09:50.560 --> 00:09:54.850
the riverlands, so that Lady Stoneheart can
capture and kill them.

00:09:54.850 --> 00:09:59.180
Tom may also hear about the transport of Lannister
prisoners, and an upcoming Lannister wedding

00:09:59.180 --> 00:10:03.500
– some fans speculate that the brotherhood
and some riverlords will free the prisoners,

00:10:03.500 --> 00:10:07.839
and crash the wedding, to massacre Freys and
Lannisters in a Red Wedding 2.0.

00:10:07.839 --> 00:10:11.790
But Stoneheart’s activities also connect
back to Robb’s will.

00:10:11.790 --> 00:10:16.589
Cause in Feast, Stoneheart travels in or near
Hag’s Mire, the place where Robb’s will

00:10:16.589 --> 00:10:21.480
is signed, then heads up into the Neck – the
same place Howland, Maege and Galbart seem

00:10:21.480 --> 00:10:22.480
to be.

00:10:22.480 --> 00:10:26.700
It seems likely that Stoneheart is involved
in a plot with these guys over Robb’s will,

00:10:26.700 --> 00:10:31.540
cause she’s not only a witness to the will,
like Maege and Galbart, but Stoneheart also

00:10:31.540 --> 00:10:38.840
has Robb’s old crown . So the power to crown
the next King in the North is in her hands.

00:10:38.840 --> 00:10:43.380
Which does raise an issue – Stoneheart might
not want to crown Jon King, because at least

00:10:43.380 --> 00:10:49.220
in life, Catelyn really doesn’t like Jon
– as a bastard son of Ned, Jon represents

00:10:49.220 --> 00:10:54.070
Ned’s infidelity to Cat . But it just so
happens that Howland Reed is the one person

00:10:54.070 --> 00:10:58.880
in the world who can tell Catelyn that Jon
isn’t really Ned’s bastard – that he’s

00:10:58.880 --> 00:11:01.550
Lyanna’s son, by Rhaegar Targaryen.

00:11:01.550 --> 00:11:07.220
Ned claimed Jon was his in order to protect
him . So Stoneheart is a bit of an angry murder

00:11:07.220 --> 00:11:09.650
zombie at the moment, and might not listen.

00:11:09.650 --> 00:11:14.230
But if Howland can change Stoneheart’s mind
about Jon, she may be happy to join in on

00:11:14.230 --> 00:11:17.589
a conspiracy to crown Jon King in the North.

00:11:17.589 --> 00:11:22.089
Lem says that Stoneheart doesn’t speak,
because her throat is cut too deep – but,

00:11:22.089 --> 00:11:27.550
he says, “she remembers” .
Another witness to Robb’s will is Edmure

00:11:27.550 --> 00:11:28.550
Tully.

00:11:28.550 --> 00:11:32.520
He’s a prisoner of the Freys at Riverrun,
but he meets with some important people.

00:11:32.520 --> 00:11:36.980
In one chapter, Jaime leaves him alone with
Tom o’ Sevens , the brotherhood spy – so

00:11:36.980 --> 00:11:40.850
it’s possible Ed shares information with
the brotherhood and Stoneheart.

00:11:40.850 --> 00:11:46.079
Later, Jaime lets Edmure enter Riverrun to
end the siege, which presents a golden opportunity

00:11:46.079 --> 00:11:51.209
to conspire with the Tully men, including
his uncle Brynden Blackfish.

00:11:51.209 --> 00:11:56.029
Brynden is loyal to House Stark , and Jaime
says he doesn’t doubt he’ll continue the

00:11:56.029 --> 00:12:00.980
fight . In the show, Brynden dies in Riverrun,
but in the books, Edmure helps him escape

00:12:00.980 --> 00:12:06.149
– so now, Brynden’s out there, somewhere,
determined to fight for House Stark – and

00:12:06.149 --> 00:12:11.110
since he speaks with his nephew Ed, he may
know about Robb’s will, and the possible

00:12:11.110 --> 00:12:13.610
plot to crown Jon Snow.

00:12:13.610 --> 00:12:19.029
Another couple of men who leave Riverrun include
Desmond Grell and Robin Ryger, the Tully master-at-arms

00:12:19.029 --> 00:12:23.519
and captain of guard . These guys choose to
join the Night’s Watch at the Wall – where

00:12:23.519 --> 00:12:25.500
Jon happens to be.

00:12:25.500 --> 00:12:30.940
Fans speculate that these trusted Tully men
may have been sent by Edmure in order to contact

00:12:30.940 --> 00:12:36.250
Jon – maybe to tell him about the conspiracy
to crown him as the heir to Robb.

00:12:36.250 --> 00:12:40.570
So this riverlands stuff is less certain than
the Manderly conspiracy.

00:12:40.570 --> 00:12:45.550
There’s no direct evidence that any of these
guys are plotting over Robb Stark’s will.

00:12:45.550 --> 00:12:50.700
But it is at least very suspicious that Maege
and Galbart – witnesses to Robb’s will

00:12:50.700 --> 00:12:56.269
– and Stoneheart – who has Robb’s crown
– go to the Neck, where Howland lives, the

00:12:56.269 --> 00:12:59.370
one guy who knows the truth of Jon’s birth.

00:12:59.370 --> 00:13:04.660
The stuff with Edmure, Brynden, Desmond and
Robin might not be related – but it is plausible

00:13:04.660 --> 00:13:10.160
that these guys are also somehow involved
in a conspiracy to crown Jon Snow.

00:13:10.160 --> 00:13:15.529
Okay, so we got the Manderly conspiracy around
Winterfell to betray the Boltons and support

00:13:15.529 --> 00:13:20.589
Rickon Stark, and a possible conspiracy in
the Neck to crown Jon Snow as Robb’s heir

00:13:20.589 --> 00:13:21.589
to the north.

00:13:21.589 --> 00:13:25.840
There’s also possibly some plotting going
on within the army that Stannis is marching

00:13:25.840 --> 00:13:27.470
on Winterfell.

00:13:27.470 --> 00:13:30.839
Part of Stannis’ army is made up of the
men he brought up from the south, but most

00:13:30.839 --> 00:13:35.699
of them are northmen – including the mountain
clansmen, some Mormonts, Glovers , and others

00:13:35.699 --> 00:13:41.130
. And the northmen don’t like Stannis – he’s
a stranger to the north, and worships a foreign

00:13:41.130 --> 00:13:47.259
god . The real reason they march in his army
is to kill Boltons and rescue Arya Stark – in

00:13:47.259 --> 00:13:52.480
the books, Ramsay marries a girl who the Boltons
say is Arya Stark, but is actually a girl

00:13:52.480 --> 00:13:53.949
called Jeyne Poole.

00:13:53.949 --> 00:13:57.949
The real Arya is still over in Braavos, but
the north doesn’t know that.

00:13:57.949 --> 00:14:01.779
Far as they’re concerned, Ned Stark’s
little girl is the clutches of Bolton’s

00:14:01.779 --> 00:14:04.550
bastard, and they’re willing to die to rescue
her.

00:14:04.550 --> 00:14:07.730
These guys are passionately loyal to House
Stark.

00:14:07.730 --> 00:14:12.660
So is it possible that they’re involved
in these conspiracies to install Rickon, or

00:14:12.660 --> 00:14:14.020
crown Jon?

00:14:14.020 --> 00:14:18.620
The best hint we’ve got is that two leaders
of the mountain clansmen, the Norrey and the

00:14:18.620 --> 00:14:23.540
Flint, come and visit Jon at the Wall, and
Jon himself thinks they must have some special

00:14:23.540 --> 00:14:28.920
reason to be there . Fans suggest that these
clansmen know about Robb’s will, and come

00:14:28.920 --> 00:14:32.889
to the Wall to judge if Jon could be a worthy
King in the North.

00:14:32.889 --> 00:14:37.300
Jon discusses his plans for the wildlings
with the clansmen, and tells them he may seem

00:14:37.300 --> 00:14:43.949
a green boy in their eyes, but he is still
a son of Eddard Stark – which may be exactly

00:14:43.949 --> 00:14:46.030
what the clansmen wanna hear.

00:14:46.030 --> 00:14:49.699
But if the clansmen are in on the plot to
crown Jon, how are they in contact with the

00:14:49.699 --> 00:14:52.670
folks in the Neck who know about the will?

00:14:52.670 --> 00:14:56.769
One possibility is that they’re in touch
with Maege Mormont through her daughter Alysane,

00:14:56.769 --> 00:14:58.820
who’s on the march with Stannis.

00:14:58.820 --> 00:15:02.440
Maege’s other daughter Lyanna is the kid
who writes that that awesome letter , and

00:15:02.440 --> 00:15:04.110
that speech in the show.

00:15:04.110 --> 00:15:08.760
Alternatively, the clansmen might be in touch
with Galbart Glover, maybe through his sister-in-law

00:15:08.760 --> 00:15:13.320
Sybelle, who’s been spending a suspiciously
large amount of time praying in the godswood

00:15:13.320 --> 00:15:18.850
– which is something Sansa does in Clash
to receive secret messages . So the clansmen

00:15:18.850 --> 00:15:21.440
might possibly know about Robb’s will.

00:15:21.440 --> 00:15:26.240
But there is another complication in that
the clansmen know Bran Stark is alive – they

00:15:26.240 --> 00:15:30.610
see him travelling north to the Wall , and
a clansman from House Liddle even meets Bran

00:15:30.610 --> 00:15:35.620
. This is important information because Bran
is King Robb’s oldest living brother – his

00:15:35.620 --> 00:15:39.930
heir if it weren’t for the will, which only
skips Bran for Jon cause Robb thought Bran

00:15:39.930 --> 00:15:40.930
is dead.

00:15:40.930 --> 00:15:45.630
It’s very telling that the clansmen don’t
tell Stannis about Bran – whatever their

00:15:45.630 --> 00:15:49.040
intentions, they’re clearly keeping secrets.

00:15:49.040 --> 00:15:53.780
So while there’s no clear evidence of any
conspiracy among the northmen in Stannis’

00:15:53.780 --> 00:15:57.950
army, there are some possible connections,
and at the least, the northmen are clearly

00:15:57.950 --> 00:16:01.130
more loyal to Stark than they are to Stannis.

00:16:01.130 --> 00:16:06.569
There are a few other northern houses to talk
about – House Karstark is an interesting

00:16:06.569 --> 00:16:07.569
one.

00:16:07.569 --> 00:16:12.400
Arnolf Karstark joins with Stannis, but secretly
plans to betray him for the Boltons.

00:16:12.400 --> 00:16:17.190
Part of his scheme is to forcibly marry the
heir to Karhold, Alys Karstark, to his son

00:16:17.190 --> 00:16:19.269
Cregan, so he can be Lord of Karhold.

00:16:19.269 --> 00:16:24.470
But Alys escapes, and the person she turns
to for protection and justice is none other

00:16:24.470 --> 00:16:29.500
than Jon Snow – she comes all the way north
to the Wall, and begs him for help, Leias

00:16:29.500 --> 00:16:33.529
him as her “only hope” as “the last
son of Eddard Stark”.

00:16:33.529 --> 00:16:38.500
There’s no evidence Alys knows about any
conspiracy, but her attitude to Jon does support

00:16:38.500 --> 00:16:43.639
the idea that the people of the north see
Jon as the inheritor of Ned Stark’s legacy,

00:16:43.639 --> 00:16:45.630
and a legitimate leader in the north.

00:16:45.630 --> 00:16:50.009
Anyway, in a sample chapter of Winds, Stannis
finds out about Arnolf’s deception, and

00:16:50.009 --> 00:16:53.540
locks up his men – so the Karstarks are
out of action for now.

00:16:53.540 --> 00:16:55.910
There’s also House Hornwood.

00:16:55.910 --> 00:17:00.420
After the deaths of Lord Halys and Daryn,
Donella becomes Lady of the Hornwood, but

00:17:00.420 --> 00:17:05.840
Ramsay forcibly marries and kills her, starving
her in a dungeon til she chews her own fingers

00:17:05.840 --> 00:17:10.790
off . Ramsay now calls himself Lord of the
Hornwood , and some Hornwood men have submitted

00:17:10.790 --> 00:17:15.870
to him, joining the Bolton army . But as Barbrey
Dustin points out, the Hornwoods haven’t

00:17:15.870 --> 00:17:21.410
forgotten what Ramsay did to Donella . There’s
no evidence of Hornwoods involved in any conspiracy,

00:17:21.410 --> 00:17:24.830
but it’s fair to say they’re not real
loyal to the Boltons.

00:17:24.830 --> 00:17:26.950
The Cerwyns and Tallharts are similar.

00:17:26.950 --> 00:17:30.830
We don’t know all that much about them,
but we do know that Roose sends Cerwyn and

00:17:30.830 --> 00:17:35.840
Tallhart men into a suicide mission to Duskendale,
and that at the sack of Winterfell, Ramsay

00:17:35.840 --> 00:17:41.640
betrays and kills Lord Cley Cerwyn and Leobald
Tallhart . Some survivors of this battle end

00:17:41.640 --> 00:17:45.930
up joining Stannis’ army , which could be
a really big deal – these men could spread

00:17:45.930 --> 00:17:50.120
the word of Ramsay’s crimes and betrayal
at Winterfell, which most of the north still

00:17:50.120 --> 00:17:52.400
believes were committed by Theon.

00:17:52.400 --> 00:17:56.520
So while we don’t know of any Cerwyn or
Tallhart involvement in any conspiracy, but

00:17:56.520 --> 00:18:02.010
the houses are, in Roose Bolton’s words,
“not to be relied on” . Really the only

00:18:02.010 --> 00:18:06.770
big northern house that probably is loyal
to House Bolton is House Ryswell.

00:18:06.770 --> 00:18:10.940
The Ryswells are tied to the Boltons by marriage,
and we see Ryswell leaders working closely

00:18:10.940 --> 00:18:15.330
with Boltons and Freys . The Ryswells did
lose men at the Red Wedding – but there

00:18:15.330 --> 00:18:19.120
are no particular hints that they’re disloyal
to the Boltons.

00:18:19.120 --> 00:18:23.900
So in the words of Roose Bolton, northern
politics in Dance is a “world of treachery

00:18:23.900 --> 00:18:28.351
and deceit” . People siding with the Boltons
aren’t really loyal to the Boltons, people

00:18:28.351 --> 00:18:33.180
siding with Stannis aren’t really loyal
to Stannis – most folks seem to want a Stark

00:18:33.180 --> 00:18:34.180
in Winterfell.

00:18:34.180 --> 00:18:37.530
But is there a Grand Northern Conspiracy?

00:18:37.530 --> 00:18:42.170
We do know Wyman Manderly is plotting to install
Rickon Stark – Robett Glover, the Flints

00:18:42.170 --> 00:18:47.070
and Lockes are in on it, and probably so are
the snow-men in Winterfell, Whoresbane and

00:18:47.070 --> 00:18:48.070
Barbrey.

00:18:48.070 --> 00:18:51.760
To the south, there’s a probable plot over
Robb’s will to crown Jon, involving Maege

00:18:51.760 --> 00:18:56.460
and Galbart and Howland, who’re connected
to Stoneheart, and Tom, and Edmure, and Brynden

00:18:56.460 --> 00:18:57.490
and the Riverrun guys.

00:18:57.490 --> 00:19:02.480
It’s also kinda possible that the mountain
clans, Alysane Mormont or Sybelle Glover are

00:19:02.480 --> 00:19:04.480
involved, themselves connected to Jon.

00:19:04.480 --> 00:19:09.840
Are all these people working together in unison,
secretly scheming to play Stannis and Roose

00:19:09.840 --> 00:19:13.950
against each other, to get vengeance on the
Boltons and Freys, and finally, to return

00:19:13.950 --> 00:19:18.420
a Stark to Winterfell, in a truly Grand Northern
Conspiracy?

00:19:18.420 --> 00:19:20.350
Are all these people connected?

00:19:20.350 --> 00:19:21.350
…Maybe.

00:19:21.350 --> 00:19:22.900
But probably not.

00:19:22.900 --> 00:19:26.280
Few reasons why – firstly, they don’t
have phones in Westeros.

00:19:26.280 --> 00:19:28.930
So it’s really hard to communicate secretly.

00:19:28.930 --> 00:19:32.430
There are messenger ravens, but we’re told
a bunch of times that it’s a bad idea to

00:19:32.430 --> 00:19:38.020
trust a secret to a bird – they can be intercepted,
or lost, and besides, letters are generally

00:19:38.020 --> 00:19:43.310
read and written by maesters, who themselves
aren’t trusted – Barbrey and Wyman specifically

00:19:43.310 --> 00:19:45.080
both question maesters.

00:19:45.080 --> 00:19:46.840
So communication’s hard.

00:19:46.840 --> 00:19:51.920
And secondly, the bigger a conspiracy is,
the less likely it is to stay secret – that’s

00:19:51.920 --> 00:19:56.920
true in the real world and in Westeros, and
we got a Westerosi example in the Karstark

00:19:56.920 --> 00:19:57.920
treachery.

00:19:57.920 --> 00:20:02.970
As far as we know, only a few Karstark men
know about Arnolf’s plan to betray Stannis,

00:20:02.970 --> 00:20:05.890
and yet, thanks to Alys, the truth gets out.

00:20:05.890 --> 00:20:09.900
Stannis himself makes a point that you can’t
keep secrets among lots and lots of people

00:20:09.900 --> 00:20:13.410
. Big grand conspiracies just aren’t that
plausible.

00:20:13.410 --> 00:20:18.690
It really looks like there are multiple different
separate plans at work here.

00:20:18.690 --> 00:20:23.160
Manderly wants to make Rickon Lord of Winterfell,
recognising Stannis as King, while Maege and

00:20:23.160 --> 00:20:26.320
Galbart presumably want to make Jon Snow King.

00:20:26.320 --> 00:20:30.740
People like Stoneheart and the mountain clansmen
have their own priorities – these seem like

00:20:30.740 --> 00:20:32.380
separate plots.

00:20:32.380 --> 00:20:37.500
So the evidence doesn’t support the idea
of one big cohesive Grand Northern Conspiracy.

00:20:37.500 --> 00:20:43.280
What it does support are several medium-sized
loosely overlapping plots in the north and

00:20:43.280 --> 00:20:44.280
riverlands.

00:20:44.280 --> 00:20:48.860
Which doesn’t have as much of a ring to
it – but still, ultimately, conclusively,

00:20:48.860 --> 00:20:52.780
yes – there are conspiracies at work in
the north.

00:20:52.780 --> 00:20:56.030
The north remembers millennia of just Stark
rule.

00:20:56.030 --> 00:21:00.400
The north remembers Bolton crimes at the Red
Wedding, and Winterfell and Hornwood.

00:21:00.400 --> 00:21:01.780
The Manderlys remember.

00:21:01.780 --> 00:21:03.340
The riverlands remember.

00:21:03.340 --> 00:21:05.170
The Neck remembers.

00:21:05.170 --> 00:21:06.440
Winterfell remembers.

00:21:06.440 --> 00:21:08.850
The clansmen remember.

00:21:08.850 --> 00:21:15.250
And by one plot or another, the Starks will
rule the north again.

00:21:15.250 --> 00:21:16.320
Thanks for watching.

00:21:16.320 --> 00:21:20.340
There are lots more complications that we
didn’t cover here – like the role of Sansa

00:21:20.340 --> 00:21:24.750
and Littlefinger , the Skagosi , Mance Rayder
and the wildlings, the pink letter and the

00:21:24.750 --> 00:21:29.511
hooded man, the location of the document signed
as Robb’s will, and of course, the white

00:21:29.511 --> 00:21:34.280
walkers and the army of the dead – will
there even be a north left to rule?

00:21:34.280 --> 00:21:37.310
We’ll talk about some of this stuff in future
videos.

